Text: Just one last push to the top!
So this will take us above...
What will we find here, I wonder.
The air somehow feels colder here...
We have to stop them from being misused.
It's chilling to see souls treated with such indifference.
The aberrance is reminiscent of the Allagan Empire.
Feral souls... I can't get used to the idea...
How could you twist a living creature like that?
Mechanical augmentation... This wouldn't have been amiss in Allag.
It appears to be enhanced with electrope!
I don't know why, but I suddenly feel a chill...
Something feels seriously off about this one...
Oh gods... His aura...it's so very wrong...
Focus, Krile! It's time to fight!
A shame this elevator doesn't go straight to the top.
Let us stay on our guard.
Gah, my head can't keep up!
It changes tactics by rearranging itself!
Have care on the weapon side!
The piece on its back has separated!
Want to get us from all directions, eh?
Is this Alexandria as it was when she lived?
A virtual domain generated by her memories...
The people really did love her.
Even the citizens have been recreated.
She truly was the people's princess...
Even back then she was close to her people...
All is right in the world...
To think that she is right there...
Whatever this is, it's going down!
The system is intervening directly in the memories...
There will be more interference. Let us remain vigilant.
Huh? Is this is still Alexandria?
What in the world has happened...?
I daresay we are come to a different time.
I know this is only a memory, but still...
This is the culmination of the Storm Surge...
This feels so real, it hurts not to help them...
This is only a memory... It's all in the past now...
I can't help but remember the future I lived...
I know... I need to remind myself it's only a memory...
That airship is shielding the other!
Whatever bars our way, we'll brush aside!
It matters not what bars our way!
\\<pant> Need a moment to catch my breath...
Another obstacle out of the way.
Are we in a different time again?
It appears to be the same place...
The war appears to have ended...
The memory banks have become unstable.
I have a bad feeling about this... Let's hurry!
The system itself may have become unstable.
It's not because of us, is it?
Let's keep a close eye on that sword and fist.
We'll find her as soon as we've dealt with this!
It's employing countermeasures against Cahciua's program!
So this is where gladiators once learned their craft...
This chill in the air... 'Tis a far cry from the desert heat.
What manner of creature lurks in these depths?
The stench of beasts... We must needs remain cautious.
This flow of aether looks promising enough. Let's dive in!
This confluence should bear us onward.
What happens if we pull this?
Perhaps we ought to loosen that winch.
The aether beckons. Let us make haste.
Let us ride the aetherial flow.
Heh! Even that brawn's no match for me!
A demon of the ninth rung? Curious...
An ogre...and a formidable one at that.
That one looks mean. Be careful!
I have a bad feeling about this...
Has that thing been sealed away all this time!?
It would be fortunate if they ran this way...
We must pray the hhetso are all right.
They may be too frightened to find us...
What if the tturuhhetso got to them!?
Where did they all come from!?
...Didn't think she'd be so quick to trade blows.
Never seen ruins like these before...
What does that do, I wonder?
By the light of the dawn!
You can't stop the flood of mortal existence!
Eyes peeled for anything brown and fluffy!
It has yet to recollect its aether.
There's no telling where this leads, but it's better than staying here.
We aren't too late, are we?
What is that? Some kind of tural vidraal?
Are we lost again? Wait, look there!
Oh gods, and it has company!
Looks like it's their problem now. Let's go.
A dragon! But surely it's no match for you.
There's something about that big tower...
Let's go and have a look.
One last push until the end!
You'll get it next time, eh?
Practice makes perfect, as they say.
That was kind of fun, actually.
A worthwhile exercise, if you ask me!
Take it away from the group!
Spread out, but mind your step!
I've got it! Let's all run clockwise!
Everyone gather at the point of impact!
Try to stand right at the edge...
Let's each take command of a tower!
Once you've recovered, get to a tower, quick!
We'll need to dodge both of these...
Take a tower, but watch your step!
Watch your step, but keep your back turned!
Keep your distance while you dodge these attacks!
Let's each handle one bomb apiece!
Worry not, I can cure you!
Stay calm and cast Esuna on each of us!
To the point of greatest density!
The land trembles before my might!
You shall be consumed by the cowardice that binds you...
You shall be twisted by the envy that drives you...
You shall be burned by the rage that controls you...
You shall be defeated by the apathy that plagues you...
You shall be smothered by the arrogance that consumes you...
The one on the left is all yours!
It's infusing the rocks with aether!
It's pierced the pillar with its tusks!
We won't fall prey to the same attack!
What's he got up his sleeve this time?
Stay calm and keep your distance!
It's up to something... On your guard!
I think we've made it angry.
This next attack will be fierce. Stay alert!
I can't even see the bottom!
It opened a hole in the ground!
Fall, and I won't be able to save you!
How deep does this hole go?
Patience will lead us to victory!
The lightning hasn't let up here either.
To think we'd find a place like this so far from Everkeep.
Even the creatures here are electrified...
The lightning rods are still operational...
I guess we've stepped into its territory.
Quite the mouthful of fangs. Don't get too close!
We've no choice but to press on!
You are a credit to your title, Vow of Resolve.
A remote facility with a secret purpose...
Hardly any signs there was ever a village here...
They were experimenting on their own...?
Is this the man in charge?
There's something unsettling about the aether here.
We won't be passing through without a fight.
The seal? The beast? What was he talking about?
Let us pray these souls are now at peace.
It keeps going. So should we.
I can hardly believe my eyes...
Ah... I think I know what awaits us.
Is there any way to stop it?
We may soon face our fiercest foe yet.
All the more reason to deal with it here and now!
A tural vidraal...no doubt about it.
We must slay it before it breaks free!
Its strength of will is overwhelming...
The wrath of the heavens is frightening indeed.
